    "extract": "Grown Ups 2 is a 2013 American comedy film starring Adam Sandler, Kevin James, Chris Rock and David Spade. The sequel to the 2010 film, Grown Ups, it was directed by Dennis Dugan, written by Sandler, Fred Wolf, and Tim Herlihy. Alongside the quartet, as well as Salma Hayek, Maya Rudolph, and Maria Bello, several actors also reprise their roles from the previous film, with Nick Swardson joining them. In the film, Lenny (Sandler) moves his family back to his hometown, where he reunites with his old friends. Together, they face bizarre situations and new enemies in the form of a local fraternity."
